claim.claim-text:
10. A method of manufacturing a semiconductor die package comprising the steps of: 
forming a package assembly including a plurality of electrically conductive leads and a housing defining a cavity for holding at least one semiconductor die, said housing including a plurality of insulative side walls and an end plate joined to the side walls, wherein each of said plurality of electrically conductive leads extend through at least one of said side walls such that an internal lead section extends within the cavity and an external lead section extends externally of said at least one side wall; 
forming a cover plate for joining to said side walls opposite said end plate, wherein said cover plate includes an aperture formed therethrough for exposing to the environment the at least one semiconductor die held in the cavity.
